Storing large arrays of quotes inside quotes collection is not very performant. Quotes should be moved to a separate collection and reference pricing assets. Maybe even use time series mongo DB collections?

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[PERF] Denormalize the latest quote onto the quote source document.
    Compass flags quoteHistory as an unbounded array. The real cost is the working set: WiredTiger
    loads the WHOLE multi-year array off disk just to satisfy the "give me the latest quote" paths
    that only $slice it to the last element. With daily/weekly/monthly cadence + the stale-dedup in
    quotes/index.py, the array is bounded in practice (no 16MB risk for decades), so the cheap,
    high-payoff fix is NOT a full restructure but denormalization:
      - Keep a top-level lastQuote: {timestamp, quote} field on the quotes doc.
      - Write it alongside the $push in flaskr/apps/quotes/index.py:77 (and importQuotes.py:79).
      - Repoint the "latest only" readers off the $slice(-1) onto the new field:
            flaskr/apps/pricing/item.py:25, flaskr/apps/pricing/listAll.py:101,
            flaskr/apps/quotes/index.py:31, plus header.py:44-45 (lastQuote timestamp).
    Result: latest-quote reads touch a tiny fixed-size field instead of dragging the full history
    through cache. Leaves history storage (and the wide-window chart read in context.py) untouched.
    This is the pragmatic alternative to the separate-collection / time-series rewrite above.

